Virginia Military Institute   About the VMI Foundation  skip to content VMI VMI Alumni Keydet Club Webcams Directories Login Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give Close Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org   Home   About   About Us About The Foundation To Advance VMI The VMI Foundation s mission is simple  to raise  steward  and invest the funds entrusted to it by members of the VMI Family for the sole purpose of advancing the Virginia Military Institute  Operating as a private  non profit corporation since 1937  the VMI Foundation annually raises tens of millions of dollars in gifts and commitments from VMI s alumni  parents  and friends as well as manages hundreds of millions of dollars in endowments  With this private money  the VMI Foundation supports the constant improvement of the Institute s academic and co curricular programs  It also supports capital improvements on Post that ensure that VMI has the high quality facilities necessary to provide a modern education and a healthful environment in which the Corps of Cadets live  learn  and compete Also  immediate gifts from donors and endowments that the VMI Foundation manages annually generate millions of dollars in financial aid  In the current academic year  private financial support constitutes one quarter of VMI s  84 5 million operating budget  and the vast majority of this comes from the VMI Foundation  This money ensures that VMI can offer the combination of rigorous academics  a demanding co curriculum  and plentiful athletic opportunities that constitute its extraordinary education  As a private entity  the VMI Foundation also provides an indirect financial benefit to the Institute by removing from it the financial burden of managing and staffing its own development office  The VMI Foundation also funds the vital work of the VMI Alumni Association and cooperates with the VMI Alumni Association and the VMI Keydet Club to strengthen the bonds within the VMI Family and the ties alumni and friends have to the Institute  In the last academic year  therefore  the VMI Foundation provided almost  28 million in direct and indirect aid to the Institute and its faculty  staff  and cadets  About The Foundation Our Mission   President s Message   Message from the CEO   Board of Trustees   Executing our Mission   History All Foundation Staff   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI UNCOMMON PURPOSE   In 1839  VMI set an uncommon course  to prepare young people for lives of service  leadership  and character  VMI cadets learn   through a rigorous military system  a demanding academic curriculum  and a robust athletic program  They leave VMI prepared to lead lives of strength  honor  and integrity   to serve their country and their communities as citizen soldiers  in times of peace and in times of deepest peril  THE VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue   Lexington  VA 24450 P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 463 2695 give vmiaa org Virginia Military Institute   About the VMI Foundation  skip to content VMI VMI Alumni Keydet Club Webcams Directories Login Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give Close Menu About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org   Home   About   About Us About The Foundation To Advance VMI The VMI Foundation s mission is simple  to raise  steward  and invest the funds entrusted to it by members of the VMI Family for the sole purpose of advancing the Virginia Military Institute  Operating as a private  non profit corporation since 1937  th