urricular programs  It also supports capital improvements on Post that ensure that VMI has the high quality facilities necessary to provide a modern education and a healthful environment in which the Corps of Cadets live  learn  and compete Also  immediate gifts from donors and endowments that the VMI Foundation manages annually generate millions of dollars in financial aid  In the current academic year  private financial support constitutes one quarter of VMI s  84 5 million operating budget  and the vast majority of this comes from the VMI Foundation  This money ensures that VMI can offer the combination of rigorous academics  a demanding co curriculum  and plentiful athletic opportunities that constitute its extraordinary education  As a private entity  the VMI Foundation also provides an indirect financial benefit to the Institute by removing from it the financial burden of managing and staffing its own development office  The VMI Foundation also funds the vital work of the VMI Alumni Association and cooperates with the VMI Alumni Association and the VMI Keydet Club to strengthen the bonds within the VMI Family and the ties alumni and friends have to the Institute  In the last academic year  therefore  the VMI Foundation provided almost  28 million in direct and indirect aid to the Institute and its faculty  staff  and cadets  About The Foundation Our Mission   President s Message   Message from the CEO   Board of Trustees   Executing our Mission   History All Foundation Staff About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org  About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Recognition Stewardship Videos Give VMI FOUNDATION Neikirk Hall   304 Letcher Avenue P O  Box 932   Lexington  VA 24450 P  800 444 1839   540 464 7328 F  540 464 4545 give vmiaa org About Us Priorities About Giving Thanks   Rec