extraordinary education  As a private entity  the VMI Foundation also provides an indirect financial benefit to the Institute by removing from it the financial burden of managing and staffing its own development office  The VMI Foundation also funds the vital work of the VMI Alumni Association and cooperates with the VMI Alumni Association and the VMI Keydet Club to strengthen the bonds within the VMI Family and the ties alumni and friends have to the Institute  In the last academic year  therefore  the VMI Foundation provided almost  28 million in direct and indirect aid to the Institute and its faculty  staff  and cadets  About The Foundation Our Mission   President s Message   Message from the CEO   Board of Trustees   Executing our Mission   History All Foundation Staff Home   About   About Us Home   About   About Us Home About      About The Foundation To Advance VMI The VMI Foundation s mission is simple  to raise  steward  and invest the funds entrusted to it by members of the VMI Family for the sole purpose of advancing the Virginia Military Institute  Operating as a private  non profit corporation since 1937  the VMI Foundation annually raises tens of millions of dollars in gifts and commitments from VMI s alumni  parents  and friends as well as manages hundreds of millions of dollars in endowments  With this private money  the VMI Foundation supports the constant improvement of the Institute s academic and co curricular programs  It also supports capital improvements on Post that ensure that VMI has the high quality facilities necessary to provide a modern education and a healthful environment in which the Corps of Cadets live  learn  and compete Also  immediate gifts from donors and endowments that the VMI Foundation manages annually generate millions of dollars in financial aid  In the current academic year  private financial support constitutes one quarter of VMI s  84 5 million operating budget  and the vast majority of this comes from the VMI Foundation  This money ensures that VMI can offer the combination of rigorous academics  a demanding co curriculum  and plentiful athletic opportunities that constitute its extraordinary education  As a private entity  the VMI Foundation also provides an indirect financial benefit to the Institute by removing from it the financial burden of managing and staffing its own development office  The VMI Foundation also funds the vital work of the VMI Alumni Association and cooperates with the VMI Alumni Association and the VMI Keydet Club to strengthen the bonds within the VMI Family and the ties alumni and friends have to the Institute  In the last academic year  therefore  the VMI Foundation provided almost  28 million in direct and indirect aid to the Institute and its faculty  staff  and cadets About The Foundation To Advance VMI The VMI Foundation s mission is simple  to raise  steward  and invest the funds entrusted to it by members of the VMI Family for the sole purpose of advancing the Virginia Military Institute Operating as a private  non profit corporation since 1937  the VMI Foundation annually raises tens of millions of dollars in gifts and commitments from VMI s alumni  parents  and friends as well as manages hundreds of millions of dollars in endowments With this private money  the VMI Foundation supports the constant improvement of the Institute s academic and co curricular programs  It also supports capital improvements on Post that ensure that VMI has the high quality facilities necessary to provide a modern education and a healthful environment in which the Corps of Cadets live  learn  and compete Also  immediate gifts from donors and endowments that the VMI Foundation manages annually generate millions of dollars in financial aid In the current academic year  private financial support constitutes one quarter of VMI s  84 5 million operating budget  and the vast majority of this comes from the VMI Foundation  This money ensures that VMI can offer the combinatio